The paper deals with clustering of signed networks, which is a topic that falls under the subfield of social network analysis. The use of a graph-based diffuse interface model formulation utilizing the Ginzburg-Landau functional is a technique that is commonly used in machine learning and optimization, which suggests that the paper could also be classified under the subfields of machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the incorporation of labelled data information, which is a common technique in semi-supervised learning, suggesting that the paper could also be classified under the subfield of semi-supervised learning (cs.SD). Finally, the paper tests its method on financial correlation matrices, which suggests that it could also be classified under the subfield of network economics (cs.NE).
